Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 13 Jan (TANJUG) -- A session of the 
Supreme Defense Council was held in Belgrade today under the 
chairmanship of FRY President Zoran Lilic, the Yugoslav 
president's military office has announced. In addition to 
members of the Supreme Defense Council -- Serbian President 
Slobodan Milosevic and Montenegrin President Momir Bulatovic -- 
the session was also attended by Yugoslav Prime Minister Radoje 
Kontic, Federal Defense Minister Pavle Bulatovic, and Lieutenant 
Colonel General Momcilo pereisic, the Yugoslav Army chief of the 
general staff. 
  The Supreme Defense Council discussed the financing of the 
Yugoslav Army and concluded that in 1994 priority should be 
given to securing the necessary financial resources to maintain 
the necessary level of combat readiness, and to improve the 
living standards of Yugoslav Army members, a statement by the 
Yugoslav president's military office says. 

